title: Manitowoc Lincoln prevails in 5 against Oshkosh West
text:
Manitowoc Lincoln prevails in 5 against Oshkosh West Tom Dombeck , HTR Media 10:59 p.m. CDT October 24, 2015 3d rendering of a Volleyball on a court with (Photo: DigtialStorm) 67 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Katie Henry wasn’t about to let her final game in the JFK Fieldhouse be a loss. 
The senior had a team high 22 kills and two blocks to help the third-seeded Manitowoc Lincoln volleyball team defeat sixth-seeded Oshkosh West 3-2 Saturday in the WIAA Division 1 regional final. 
The Ships fell behind 2-1 before running off two straight wins to prevail by scores of 22-25, 25-18, 22-25, 28-26, 15-8. 
The crucial set was the fourth, with Lincoln leading 18-9 before being tested to the limits by Oshkosh. 
“It was all about rotation,” Lincoln coach Mary Beth Dixon said. “When Henry was in the rotation they couldn’t stop her, but when she was it out it proved harder to get kills. I’m proud that they were able to hold on.” 
Also having huge nights for the Ships were Mallory Dixon (54 assists, 13 digs, two aces), Cassidy Mrotek (24 digs, 12 kills), Sarah Greene (20 digs, 12 kills) and Rayna Figueroa (21 digs). 
Lincoln will play No. 2 Neenah Thursday at Oshkosh West in a sectional semifinal, having lost both meetings with the Rockets this season. 
“We played them tough twice,” Dixon said of her team. “We need everyone to step up or we need another performance like Henry’s tonight if we want to do well. There’s no cake walks at this point.” 67 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://htrne.ws/1N0eCcs TOP VIDEOS
